From BONG Eric Bong Subject Re Boom Dog attack In article wrote What worked for me on my was to lean towards the dog as I modulated throttle to keep my ankle just ahead of his After a few seconds of warm pipe firmly wedged on his shoulder he turned his face sideways to see what was so warm and got his mouth nose muzzle burned on the One yip and he veered away never to chase me Nice ridin' I use the California DMV recommended technique slow as you aproach said dog and wick it up as you I've often contemplated putting the boot in said dog's muzzle as I open the throttle but have never tried I figgure the impact would unballance me and I'd dump the A bicycling technique I've employed was to use my frame mounted tire pump to fend off dog On one occasion I was attacked by a pack of four dogs at once while peddaling up a steep I lost my right sock but no I complained to the local Animal Control department after complaining to the owner of the dogs to no affect about the dogs no more dogs no more The telephone worked much better than the tire Eric Bong DoD